      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "On this 24th day of August A.D. 1867, before me H. S. Park, a Notary Public within and for the County and State aforesaid, personally came and appeared Peyton Bibb aged 28 years, a resident of the City of Henderson in the State of Kentucky, who, being by me duly sworn according to law, on oath declares that \"Was late 1st Sergt Co. \"G\" in the Use Hundred & Eighteenth Regiment United States Colored Infantry and was acquainted with Aaron Chambers decd Late a private in Same Company & Regiment who died in the United States service in the State of Virginia on the Sixth day of Nov 1864 from the Effect of Dearborn which he incurred in the service aforesaid under the following circumstances that he had the dearer had very bad in company quarter and we were ordered to March on day above mentioned and he was sent to field Hospital and died before reaching Hospital that he was a man of sound physical when he entered the army and a good soldier a man of steady & sober habits. That I have no interest in this matter.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 240,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 120
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "P. H. A. H. Satt Sergt Co. \"G\" 110th U.S.C.T. Inf.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 360,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 20
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Sworn to and subscribed before me, this 27th day of August in the year 1867, and I hereby certify that the affiant is a respectable and credible person and resides as stated; that I believe his statements are correct and worthy of full faith and credit; that I have no interest in this matter. I further certify that the foregoing affidavit was read over, fully explained to, and understood by the affiant before the signing and execution thereof, and also that the affiant is the identical party represented as making the affidavit.",
